groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: Geologicache
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:short_description: Traditional cache within the confines of Meadow Lane Park, Vienna, VA
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description:
Small container with log book and some rocks, of course (it's not called Geologicache for nothing!) When the weather is nice there will probably be plenty of Muggles. A few thorns and poison ivy to watch out for too.

NOTICE: Please be respectful of the park hours. FCPA Parks are open dawn to dusk unless otherwise posted. If you enter the park after hours you are trespassing. If you are stopped you can be ticketed, or arrested and you will jeopardize the future of geocaching in the parks. Do NOT hunt this cache at night!

***Congrats to pattilax on FTF***

After 1 year, 74 finds, 2 DNFs.

After 2 years, 108 finds, 5 DNFs.

After 3 years, 160 finds, 5 DNFs.

After 4 years, 192 finds, 7 DNFs.

groundspeak:log.groundspeak:text: Quick find on a chilly morning. TFTC
